House Resolution 146
By: Representatives Lupton of the 83rd and Tran of the 80th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Gina Gallois; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Gina Gallois has dedicated her career to educating and inspiring children
3 through literature, using her passion for storytelling to foster a greater appreciation for
4 wildlife and neurodiversity; and
5 WHEREAS, her lifelong environmentalism and love of animals led her to recognize a
6 widespread lack of awareness about opossums in 2019, motivating her to take action by
7 visiting numerous classrooms and nature centers to share her appreciation for misunderstood
8 and under-represented critters; and
9 WHEREAS, in recognition of her contributions to environmental education, the Oatland
10 Island Wildlife Center in Savannah, Georgia, inaugurated a permanent storybook trail in
11 2024 featuring Mama Opossum's Misadventures in both English and Spanish, allowing
12 visitors to engage with her work while learning about local wildlife; and
13 WHEREAS, as the mother of two autistic children, she and her husband, Fabien, have
14 embraced and advocated for neurodiversity, and she has used her experiences to create such
