15 wonderful works as Quantum Possum, which celebrates the diverse ways in which
16 individuals experience the world; and
17 WHEREAS, her Awesome Opossum Stories series, which introduces young readers to
18 fundamental concepts such as opposites, counting, comparison, and alphabet action verbs
19 through engaging narratives, has been honored with the prestigious Mom's Choice Gold
20 Award; and
21 WHEREAS, her distinguished literary contributions further include the Bug Club Story
22 series, featuring Cicada City and Moth Metamorphosis, as well as I Don't Want to be Scary
23 on Halloween and Cats and Dogs Make the Best of Friends; and
24 WHEREAS, as an advocate for multilingual literacy and a former professor of French
25 language and literature, she has ensured her books are available in French and Spanish in
26 addition to English; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this distinguished individual be
28 appropriately honored.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize and commend Gina Gallois for her outstanding
31 contributions to childhood education, advocacy, and environmentalism as well as extend best
32 wishes for future health and happiness.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Gina
35 Gallois.
